.Dd May 9, 2026
.Dt NOBODY 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm nobody
.Nd run agents without ambient authority
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Cm run
.Op Fl p Ar policy
.Fl -
.Ar command
.Op Ar argument ...
.Nm
.Cm policy simulate
.Ar policy
.Fl -
.Ar action
.Op Ar argument ...
.Nm
.Cm trace show
.Op Ar latest | file
.Op Fl -jsonl
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a least-privilege execution runtime for AI agents.
The current prototype reads a TOML policy, evaluates process and environment
capability decisions, runs the permitted command with a filtered environment,
appends structured JSONL trace events, and simulates filesystem decisions for
diagnostics.
.Pp
It is not yet a security sandbox.
Filesystem, network, MCP, and browser-control enforcement are planned but are
not implemented in this milestone.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl p , Fl -policy Ar file
Read policy from
.Ar file .
The default is
.Pa nobody.toml .
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Pa nobody.toml
Default policy file.
.It Pa .nobody/runs/latest.jsonl
Default trace file.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bd -literal
nobody run -- echo hello
nobody run --policy nobody.toml -- echo hello
nobody policy check nobody.toml
nobody policy simulate nobody.toml -- fs.read .env
nobody policy simulate nobody.toml -- process.exec curl
nobody trace show latest
nobody trace show latest --jsonl
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Pa docs/policy.md ,
.Pa docs/trace.md ,
.Pa docs/roadmap.md
